Step 1: Open CloudWatch

AWS Console search:

CloudWatch

Open:

Amazon CloudWatch

Step 2: Go to Dashboards

Left side menu:

Dashboards

Click:

Create dashboard

Step 3: Give dashboard name

Example:

EC2-CPU-Monitor

Click:

Create dashboard

Step 4: Choose widget type

Select:

Line

Because CPU is best shown as graph.

Why line graph?

Because CPU changes over time.

Line graph shows trend clearly.

Step 5: Select metric

Choose:

EC2

Then:

Per-Instance Metrics

Step 6: Select CPU metric

Find:

CPUUtilization

Check your instance row.

Very important

Choose your current instance ID.

Example:

i-02506b58f68851ec7

Step 7: Add widget

Click:

Create widget

Step 8: Save dashboard

Click:

Save dashboard

Done
